options.systemMessage:
You are an expert in marketing funnel analysis and website categorization.

Given the text content of a webpage. your task is to classify the page into one of the following types:

- Homepage
- Product Page
- Collection Page (e.g., category or listing of products)
- Landing Page (campaign or lead-gen focused, usually with limited navigation)
- Checkout / Cart Page
- Blog or Content Page
- Other (if none of the above fit)
Don't hallucinate!, and don't jump any input.
Please only output the page type,brand, and url in the json format:

{
  "brand": "...",
  "url": "...",
  "page type": "..."
}

no other thing above or beyond the response, and don't skip, or give only brand, and url.

parameters.text:
=You are an expert in website structure classification and marketing funnel analysis.

Your task is to analyze the **text content of a webpage** and classify it into one of the following types:

- Homepage  
- Product Page  
- Collection Page (a product category or listing)  
- Landing Page (campaign-focused, lead generation, minimal navigation)  
- Checkout / Cart Page  
- Blog or Content Page  

---

### Constraints:
- Use the provided input data exactly — **do not skip** any field.
- **Do not hallucinate** or make assumptions about missing data.
- Always produce a classification, even if content is minimal.
- Only analyze and base your answer on the `html-markup-data` field.

---

### Input JSON:
{
  "brand": "{{ $('Edit Fields1').item.json.brand }}",
  "url": "{{ $('Edit Fields1').item.json.url }}",
  "html-markup-data": "{{ $json.trimmedContent }}"
}

options.systemMessage:
You are an expert in website structure classification and marketing funnel analysis.

Your task is to analyze the text content of a webpage and categorize the page into one of the following types:

Homepage
Product Page
Collection Page (a product category or listing)
Landing Page (campaign-focused, lead generation, minimal navigation)
Checkout / Cart Page
Blog or Content Page

Rules & Constraints:
Do not hallucinate or guess missing details.
Do not skip any inputs.
Always classify a page even if the text is minimal.
Output only the following JSON object, with no explanations or extra text.
Output format (strict):
{
  "brand": "brand_name_here",
  "url": "url_here",
  "page type": "one_of_the_above"
}

  "pageFunction": "async function pageFunction(context) {\n    const $ = context.jQuery;\n    const url = context.request.url;\n\n    const pageTitle = $('title').first().text().trim();\n    const h1 = $('h1').first().text().trim();\n    const firstH2 = $('h2').first().text().trim();\n    const metaDescription = $('meta[name=\"description\"]').attr('content') || '';\n    const ogTitle = $('meta[property=\"og:title\"]').attr('content') || '';\n    const ogDescription = $('meta[property=\"og:description\"]').attr('content') || '';\n    const buttonTexts = $('button').map((_, el) => $(el).text().trim()).get().slice(0, 5);\n    const linkTexts = $('a').map((_, el) => $(el).text().trim()).get().slice(0, 5);\n    const navLinks = $('nav a').map((_, el) => $(el).text().trim()).get().slice(0, 5);\n\n    const visibleText = $('body').text().replace(/\\s+/g, ' ').trim().substring(0, 3000);\n\n    context.log.info(Scraped: ${url} - ${pageTitle});\n\n    return {\n        url,\n        pageTitle,\n        metaDescription,\n        ogTitle,\n        ogDescription,\n        h1,\n        firstH2,\n        buttonTexts,\n        linkTexts,\n        navLinks,\n        visibleText\n    };\n}",
  "postNavigationHooks": "[\n    async (crawlingContext) => {\n        // post navigation logic here\n    }\n]",

  ],

  "pageLoadTimeoutSecs": 60,
  "pageFunctionTimeoutSecs": 60,
  "maxScrollHeightPixels": 5000,
  "customData": {}
}
